As shock from the morning's horrendous events subsided, many began to express
anger both online and offline. Throughout the day, people gathered to protest
police brutality in Kyiv and other cities.The pictures of these spontaneous
protests were circulated widely on social media. [Radio
Svoboda](https://twitter.com/radiosvoboda/) (RFE/RL) shared this
[photo](https://twitter.com/radiosvoboda/statuses/406826285696946176) on
Twitter:

> Молодь на Майдані незалежності, сидить під йолкою в знак протесту.
> [#євромайдан](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23%D1%94%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B0%D0%B9%D0%B4%D0%B0%D0%BD&src=hash)
> [pic.twitter.com/mF5sqI3hEu](http://t.co/mF5sqI3hEu)
>
> — Радіо Свобода (@radiosvoboda) [November 30,
> 2013](https://twitter.com/radiosvoboda/statuses/406826285696946176)

> Youth on the Independence Square, sitting under the [Christmas tree] to
> express their protest

